summary: Completed comprehensive frontend testing of Aircabio airport transfer booking website. Major improvement from previous iteration - native HTML date picker now working perfectly. Backend APIs remain 100% functional. Critical admin login issue prevents full admin dashboard testing.

ui_bugs.issue: Login form submits but doesn't authenticate - stays on login page without error messages
ui_bugs.impact: Prevents admin dashboard access and management functionality

ui_bugs.issue: Search results show blank content when accessed directly - state management issue

integration_issues.issue: Frontend login form not properly integrating with backend auth API despite API working
Cannot complete vehicle selection due to search results state issue

passed_tests: Homepage loads with booking engine visible
Native HTML date picker working perfectly (MAJOR FIX from previous iteration)
Booking form fields can be filled (pickup, dropoff, date, time, passengers, luggage, flight number)
Search vehicles button triggers navigation to search results
Vehicle quotes display correctly in search results
Fleet page displays vehicle cards with images and details
Navigation links work (Our Fleet, About Us, FAQ, Contact)
Footer legal links work (Terms & Conditions, Privacy Policy, Cancellation Policy)
Customer registration page loads and form can be filled
All backend APIs (11/11) - vehicles, pricing, quotes, auth, bookings, admin stats
action_item_for_main_agent: Fix critical admin login authentication issue - form submits but doesn't process login/redirect to admin dashboard. Also investigate search results state management for direct URL access. The native HTML date picker fix was successful and booking engine now works perfectly.
